            "text": "Food cost variance percentage is actual food cost minus theoretical food cost, divided by sales, multiplied by 100. An outlet with Rs 4.2 lakh of actual consumption against a recipe-based theoretical cost of Rs 3.9 lakh on sales of Rs 12 lakh shows a variance of 2.5 per cent. Anything above 2 per cent signals wastage, theft or portion drift."
          }
